    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-28T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-28T06:00:00-05:00" n="377"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/839: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-28T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 28, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 28—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. The Department may consider conveying informally to the new Greek Minister
                    before his presentation the fact that I have spoken to the Hellenic Foreign
                    Minister of the unfortunate impression which the executions would create in the
                    United States and that their accomplishment would cast a shadow on the usually
                    friendly reception of a new Greek Envoy and cause personal reversions [<hi
                        rend="italic">aversions?</hi>] to the President and to him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
